/-- **The FejГ©rвҖ“Poitou test function** (introduced 2026-07-23 for the
decomposition of `odlyzko_rootDiscr_totallyComplex`): the triangular
FejГ©r kernel `x вҶҰ max (1 - |x|/6) 0` of half-width `6`.  It is even,
nonnegative, satisfies `f 0 = 1`, has compact support `[-6, 6]`,
integral `3` over `(0, вҲһ)`, and nonnegative Fourier transform
`t вҶҰ 6В·(sin (3t)/(3t))ВІ` вҖ” exactly the admissibility conditions of
Poitou's unconditional explicit-formula inequality (G. Poitou, *Sur
les petits discriminants*, SГ©m. DelangeвҖ“PisotвҖ“Poitou 18 (1976/77),
exp. 6, inequality (8) and Proposition 5, p. 6-08). -/
noncomputable def odlyzkoTestFn (x : в„қ) : в„қ := max (1 - |x| / 6) 0

/-- **The PoitouвҖ“Mellin transform of the FejГ©r test function**
(introduced 2026-07-23 for the decomposition of
`poitou_explicit_formula_bound`): the pairing
`ОҰ(s) = вҲ«_в„қ (f(x)/cosh(x/2))В·e^{(sвҲ’1/2)x} dx` with `f = odlyzkoTestFn`,
i.e. the Mellin transform (2) of G. Poitou, *Sur les petits
discriminants*, SГ©m. DelangeвҖ“PisotвҖ“Poitou 18 (1976/77), exp. 6, at the
test function `F = f/cosh(x/2)` of its Proposition 5.  Since `f` is
supported in `[-6, 6]`, `ОҰ` is entire and bounded on every vertical
strip; on the boundary lines `Re s вҲҲ {0, 1}` of the critical strip its
real part is the nonnegative FejГ©r transform
`вҲ« f(x)В·cos(tx) dx = 2В·sinВІ(3t)/(3tВІ)`. -/
noncomputable def poitouPhi (s : в„Ӯ) : в„Ӯ :=
  вҲ« x : в„қ, ((odlyzkoTestFn x / Real.cosh (x / 2) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) *
    Complex.exp ((s - 1 / 2) * (x : в„Ӯ))

/-- **The prime-ideal term of Poitou's explicit formula at the FejГ©r
test function** (introduced 2026-07-23):
`4В·ОЈ_{рқ”ӯ, mвүҘ1} log Nрқ”ӯ В· f(mВ·log Nрқ”ӯ)/(1 + Nрқ”ӯ^m)` over the nonzero prime
ideals `рқ”ӯ` of `рқ’Ә_K`, with `f = odlyzkoTestFn` вҖ” the ultrametric term
`(4/n)В·ОЈ_{рқ”ӯ,m} вҖҰ` of inequality (8) of Poitou (exp. 6, p. 6-08)
multiplied by `n`.  Every summand is nonnegative
(`poitouPrimeTerm_nonneg` below), which is what legitimizes dropping
this term in the bound; since `f` vanishes beyond `6`, only the
finitely many pairs with `Nрқ”ӯ^m < eвҒ¶ = 403.42вҖҰ` contribute. -/
noncomputable def poitouPrimeTerm (K : Type*) [Field K] [NumberField K] : в„қ :=
  4 * вҲ‘' (P : {P : Ideal (NumberField.RingOfIntegers K) // P.IsPrime вҲ§ P вү  вҠҘ})
      (m : в„•),
    Real.log (Ideal.absNorm P.1) / (1 + (Ideal.absNorm P.1 : в„қ) ^ (m + 1)) *
      odlyzkoTestFn (((m : в„қ) + 1) * Real.log (Ideal.absNorm P.1))

/-- **Nonnegativity of the prime-ideal term** (PROVEN 2026-07-23):
every summand of `poitouPrimeTerm` is a product of nonnegatives
(`log Nрқ”ӯ вүҘ 0`, a positive denominator, and `odlyzkoTestFn вүҘ 0`), so
the sum is nonnegative вҖ” `tsum` of a nonnegative family is nonnegative
whether or not it converges.  This is the legitimacy of dropping the
ultrametric term of Poitou's inequality (8). -/
theorem poitouPrimeTerm_nonneg (K : Type*) [Field K] [NumberField K] :
    0 вүӨ poitouPrimeTerm K := by
  refine mul_nonneg (by norm_num) (tsum_nonneg fun P => tsum_nonneg fun m => ?_)
  refine mul_nonneg (div_nonneg (Real.log_natCast_nonneg _) (by positivity)) ?_
  rw [odlyzkoTestFn]
  exact le_max_right _ _

/-- **The Hecke continuation package for the Dedekind zeta function**
(interface designed 2026-07-23 as the sound cut of the deep
explicit-formula leaf `dedekind_explicit_formula_fejer`): the entire
completed zeta `Оҫ_K(s) = s(sвҲ’1)В·Z_K(s)`, where
`Z_K(s) = |d_K|^{s/2}В·О“_в„қ(s)^{rвӮҒ}В·О“_в„Ӯ(s)^{rвӮӮ}В·О¶_K(s)` is the completed
Dedekind zeta function (J. Neukirch, *Algebraic Number Theory*,
VII (5.10), with `О“_в„қ(s) = ПҖ^{-s/2}О“(s/2)` and
`О“_в„Ӯ(s) = 2В·(2ПҖ)^{-s}О“(s)` from VII В§4), together with EXACTLY the
analytic facts consumed by the contour argument of Poitou's
Propositions 1вҖ“3 (G. Poitou, *Sur les petits discriminants*,
SГ©m. DelangeвҖ“PisotвҖ“Poitou 18 (1976/77), exp. 6, pp. 6-01вҖ“6-06).
Field-by-field truth and role:

* `xi`, `differentiable`: `Z_K` is meromorphic with only simple poles
  at `0` and `1` (Hecke; Neukirch VII (5.10)), so `s(sвҲ’1)Z_K(s)` is
  ENTIRE вҖ” carrying `Оҫ` rather than the meromorphic `Z_K` makes every
  field a statement about a total function.
* `eq_of_one_lt_re`: the defining formula on the half-plane of
  absolute convergence, tying `Оҫ` to the pin's raw Dirichlet series
  `NumberField.dedekindZeta`.  By the identity theorem this field
  determines `xi` uniquely, so all other fields вҖ” and any per-instance
  theorem stated about a `pkg` below вҖ” are facts about THE completed
  zeta, not about an arbitrary choice: the cut cannot smuggle in a
  degenerate instance.
* `funcEq`: Hecke's functional equation `Z_K(s) = Z_K(1вҲ’s)` (Neukirch
  VII (5.10)) in `Оҫ`-form; `(1вҲ’s)((1вҲ’s)вҲ’1) = s(sвҲ’1)` makes the two
  normalizations agree.
* `conj_symm`: Schwarz reflection `Оҫ(sМ„) = conj (Оҫ(s))` вҖ” true on
  `re s > 1` since every factor of `eq_of_one_lt_re` has real
  coefficients, hence everywhere by the identity theorem.  Pairs the
  zeros `ПҒ` and `ПҒМ„` with equal multiplicities in the symmetric
  truncations of the zero sum.
* `ne_zero_of_one_lt_re`: Euler-product nonvanishing (Neukirch
  VII (5.2)) times nonvanishing of `О“`, of `s(sвҲ’1)`, and of powers of
  positive reals.  (Nonvanishing on the closed boundary line
  `re s = 1` вҖ” de la VallГ©e Poussin for `О¶_K`, plus the nonzero
  class-number-formula residue at `s = 1` itself вҖ” is deliberately NOT
  a field: it is derivable from this interface together with the
  pin's `NumberField.tendsto_sub_one_mul_dedekindZeta_nhdsGT`, and
  belongs inside the eventual proof of the zero-sum leaf
  `DedekindContinuation.fejer_zero_sum_tendsto`.)
* `growth`: the order-one bound `вҖ–Оҫ(s)вҖ– вүӨ exp(CВ·вҖ–sвҖ–В·log вҖ–sвҖ–)` off the
  disc `вҖ–sвҖ– < 2` (S. Lang, *Algebraic Number Theory*, XIII В§5): by
  Stirling on the archimedean factors and the trivial bound
  `|О¶_K(s)| вүӨ О¶(re s)^n` on `re s вүҘ 2`, extended by `funcEq` and
  PhragmГ©nвҖ“LindelГ¶f to the intermediate strip.  This single true
  growth field is what the Jensen-formula zero counting
  `N(T+1) вҲ’ N(T) = O(log T)` and Landau's horizontal estimates
  (Poitou p. 6-02, citing E. Landau, *Algebraische Zahlen*, p. 122)
  will be built from вҖ” mathlib has no Hadamard factorization, so the
  zero-sum leaf must manufacture those counts from this bound. -/
structure DedekindContinuation (K : Type*) [Field K] [NumberField K] where
  /-- The entire completed Dedekind zeta `Оҫ_K(s) = s(sвҲ’1)В·Z_K(s)`. -/
  xi : в„Ӯ вҶ’ в„Ӯ
  /-- `Оҫ_K` is entire (Hecke's theorem, Neukirch VII (5.10)). -/
  differentiable : Differentiable в„Ӯ xi
  /-- On `re s > 1` the completed zeta is
  `s(sвҲ’1)В·|d_K|^{s/2}В·О“_в„қ(s)^{rвӮҒ}В·О“_в„Ӯ(s)^{rвӮӮ}В·О¶_K(s)`. -/
  eq_of_one_lt_re : вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, 1 < s.re вҶ’
    xi s = s * (s - 1) * Complex.ofReal |(NumberField.discr K : в„қ)| ^ (s / 2) *
      ((Real.pi : в„Ӯ) ^ (-s / 2) * Complex.Gamma (s / 2)) ^
        NumberField.InfinitePlace.nrRealPlaces K *
      ((2 : в„Ӯ) * ((2 * Real.pi : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) ^ (-s) * Complex.Gamma s) ^
        NumberField.InfinitePlace.nrComplexPlaces K *
      NumberField.dedekindZeta K s
  /-- The functional equation `Оҫ_K(1 вҲ’ s) = Оҫ_K(s)`. -/
  funcEq : вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, xi (1 - s) = xi s
  /-- Schwarz reflection: the Dirichlet coefficients are real. -/
  conj_symm : вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, xi ((starRingEnd в„Ӯ) s) = (starRingEnd в„Ӯ) (xi s)
  /-- Euler-product nonvanishing on the open half-plane `re s > 1`. -/
  ne_zero_of_one_lt_re : вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, 1 < s.re вҶ’ xi s вү  0
  /-- `Оҫ_K` has order one: `вҖ–Оҫ_K(s)вҖ– вүӨ exp(CВ·вҖ–sвҖ–В·log вҖ–sвҖ–)` for
  `вҖ–sвҖ– вүҘ 2`. -/
  growth : вҲғ C : в„қ, 0 < C вҲ§ вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, 2 вүӨ вҖ–sвҖ– вҶ’
    вҖ–xi sвҖ– вүӨ Real.exp (C * вҖ–sвҖ– * Real.log вҖ–sвҖ–)

