/-- **Hecke's thetaвҖ“Mellin `WeakFEPair` family of the class group**
(DECOMPOSED 2026-07-24, assembly PROVEN вҖ” the field-by-field
`WeakFEPair` instantiation, following the pattern of
`Mathlib.NumberTheory.LSeries.HurwitzZetaEven`, on top of the analytic
kernel leaf `heckeThetaKernel_exists` and the PROVEN
`classIdealCount_LSeriesSummable`/`weakFEPair_lambdaZero_congr`): from
the `n`-dimensional lattice theta law `hОё` (verbatim
`zlattice_theta_transform`) produce, for every ideal class `C`, a
`WeakFEPair` `P C` вҖ” mathlib's abstract Mellin/functional-equation
machine (`Mathlib.NumberTheory.LSeries.AbstractFuncEq`) вҖ” with weight
`k = 1/2`, root number `Оө = 1`, shared constant term `fвӮҖ = gвӮҖ = ПҒ`,
the `ОӣвӮҖ`-level functional equation pairing `C` with
`[рқ”Ў]CвҒ»В№ = dedekindDualClass K C`, exponentially decaying kernels on
`[1, вҲһ)`, and the `re s > 1` Mellin identification
`Оӣ(s/2) = |d_K|^{s/2}В·О“_в„қ(s)^{rвӮҒ}В·О“_в„Ӯ(s)^{rвӮӮ}В·L(a_C, s)` with bundled
