decaying kernels** (sorry node, stated 2026-07-24 вҖ” the Lang XIII В§5
growth leaf of `heckeClassZeta_of_zlattice_theta`): for a
`WeakFEPair` of weight `k = 1/2` whose kernels approach their
constant terms exponentially fast on `[1, вҲһ)`, the pole-cleared
completed Mellin transform `s(sвҲ’1)В·Оӣ(s/2)` is of order one:
`вҖ–s(sвҲ’1)В·Оӣ(s/2)вҖ– вүӨ exp(BВ·вҖ–sвҖ–В·log вҖ–sвҖ–)` off the disc `вҖ–sвҖ– < 2`.

Intended proof, in three regions (S. Lang, *Algebraic Number
Theory*, XIII В§5; the pin has no Hadamard theory, so this is
elementary integral estimation):

* `re s вүҘ 2`: `Оӣ(s/2)` is the convergent Mellin integral of `f вҲ’ fвӮҖ`
  (`WeakFEPair.hasMellin`, `re (s/2) > 1/2 = P.k`); split at `t = 1`:
  the `(0,1]` piece is uniformly `O(1)` for `re s вүҘ 2` by the
  `t^{вҲ’1/2}` blow-up bound `WeakFEPair.hf_zero'`, and the `[1,вҲһ)`
  piece is bounded via `hf` by
  `AВ·вҲ«_1^вҲһ e^{вҲ’at}В·t^{Пғ/2вҲ’1} dt вүӨ AВ·max(1,aвҒ»В№)^{Пғ/2}В·О“(Пғ/2)` with
  `О“(x) вүӨ x^x = exp(xВ·log x)` for `x вүҘ 1` (elementary from
  `Real.Gamma_le_self_rpow`-style estimates or the integral
  definition), all absorbed into `exp(CВ·вҖ–sвҖ–В·log вҖ–sвҖ–)`.
* `re s вүӨ вҲ’1`: reflect through `WeakFEPair.functional_equation`,
  `Оӣ(k вҲ’ z) = Оө вҖў P.symm.Оӣ z` at `z = 1/2 вҲ’ s/2` (so
  `re z вүҘ 3/4 > 1/2`), and apply the first region's estimate to
  `P.symm`, whose `f`-kernel is `P.g` (hypothesis `hg`), using
  `вҖ–1 вҲ’ sвҖ– вүӨ 1 + вҖ–sвҖ– вүӨ 2вҖ–sвҖ–` and the fixed constant `вҖ–ОөвҖ–`.
* strip `вҲ’1 вүӨ re s вүӨ 2`, `вҖ–sвҖ– вүҘ 2`: write
  `Оӣ(s/2) = ОӣвӮҖ(s/2) вҲ’ (2/s)В·fвӮҖ вҲ’ (Оө/(1/2 вҲ’ s/2))В·gвӮҖ`
  (`WeakFEPair.ОӣвӮҖ_eq`); the pole corrections are bounded since
  `вҖ–sвҖ– вүҘ 2` keeps `s` at distance `вүҘ 1` from `0` and `1`, and
  `ОӣвӮҖ = mellin f_modif` is BOUNDED on the closed strip
  `вҲ’1/2 вүӨ re z вүӨ 1`: split the integral at `1` and use the all-order
  decay of `f_modif` at `0вҒә` and `вҲһ`
  (`WeakFEPair.hf_zero`/`hf_modif_top` at exponents clearing the
  strip) вҖ” alternatively PhragmГ©nвҖ“LindelГ¶f
  (`PhragmenLindelof.horizontal_strip`, already imported; the PROVEN
  Poitou strip-positivity section of this file has the technique in
  Lean).  Combine, absorbing the polynomial factor
  `вҖ–s(sвҲ’1)вҖ– вүӨ (вҖ–sвҖ–+1)ВІ` into the exponential
  (`Real.log вҖ–sвҖ– вүҘ Real.log 2 > 0` on `вҖ–sвҖ– вүҘ 2`). -/
theorem weakFEPair_growth (P : WeakFEPair в„Ӯ) (hk : P.k = 1 / 2)
    (A a : в„қ) (ha : 0 < a)
    (hf : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 1 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҖ–P.f t - P.fвӮҖвҖ– вүӨ A * Real.exp (-a * t))
    (hg : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 1 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҖ–P.g t - P.gвӮҖвҖ– вүӨ A * Real.exp (-a * t)) :
    вҲғ B : в„қ, 0 < B вҲ§ вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, 2 вүӨ вҖ–sвҖ– вҶ’
      вҖ–s * (s - 1) * P.Оӣ (s / 2)вҖ– вүӨ Real.exp (B * вҖ–sвҖ– * Real.log вҖ–sвҖ–) := by
  sorry

/-- **Hecke's per-ideal-class thetaвҖ“Mellin machine, conditioned on
lattice Poisson summation** (DECOMPOSED 2026-07-24, assembly PROVEN вҖ”
its sole hypothesis `hОё` is verbatim the Poisson leaf
`zlattice_theta_transform`, and its conclusion is verbatim
`completedClassZeta_exists`).

The Neukirch VII В§В§3вҖ“5 route is cut at mathlib's abstract
Mellin/functional-equation interface: the leaf `heckeFEPair_exists`
(sorried above) packages the whole ideal-lattice/unit-domain/Mellin
analysis into a class-indexed family `P` of `WeakFEPair`s (weight
`1/2`, root number `1`, shared constant term `ПҒ`, `ОӣвӮҖ`-level
functional equation pairing `C` with `[рқ”Ў]CвҒ»В№`, exponentially decaying
kernels, and the `re s > 1` identification of `Оӣ(s/2)` with the
completed partial zeta), and the leaf `weakFEPair_growth` (sorried
above) supplies the Lang XIII В§5 order-one bound for any such pair.

The assembly here is pure complex algebra over the `WeakFEPair` API:
the completed partial zeta is DEFINED as the entire function

`Z C s := sВ·(sвҲ’1)В·(P C).ОӣвӮҖ (s/2) + 2ПҒ`,

which by `WeakFEPair.ОӣвӮҖ_eq` (`ОӣвӮҖ = Оӣ + fвӮҖ/s + ОөВ·gвӮҖ/(kвҲ’s)`) agrees
with `sВ·(sвҲ’1)В·(P C).Оӣ (s/2)` at every `s вҲү {0, 1}` вҖ” the two pole
corrections contribute `2(sвҲ’1)ПҒ вҲ’ 2sПҒ + 2ПҒ = 0` exactly because the
constant terms are equal and `Оө = 1`.  Entirety is
`WeakFEPair.differentiable_ОӣвӮҖ`; the `re s > 1` formula and the growth
bound transfer through the off-`{0,1}` identity (`re s > 1` and
`вҖ–sвҖ– вүҘ 2` each exclude `0` and `1`); the functional equation is the
`ОӣвӮҖ`-level one under `(1вҲ’s)/2 = 1/2 вҲ’ s/2`. -/
theorem heckeClassZeta_of_zlattice_theta (K : Type*) [Field K] [NumberField K]
    (hОё : вҲҖ (E : Type) [NormedAddCommGroup E] [InnerProductSpace в„қ E]
      [FiniteDimensional в„қ E] [MeasurableSpace E] [BorelSpace E]
      (L : Submodule в„Ө E) [DiscreteTopology L] [IsZLattice в„қ L]
      (t : в„қ), 0 < t вҶ’
      вҲ‘' v : L, Real.exp (-Real.pi * tвҒ»В№ * вҖ–(v : E)вҖ– ^ 2) =
        (ZLattice.covolume L)вҒ»В№ * t ^ ((Module.finrank в„қ E : в„қ) / 2) *
          вҲ‘' w : LinearMap.BilinForm.dualSubmodule (innerвӮ— E) L,
            Real.exp (-Real.pi * t * вҖ–(w : E)вҖ– ^ 2)) :
    вҲғ Z : ClassGroup (NumberField.RingOfIntegers K) вҶ’ в„Ӯ вҶ’ в„Ӯ,
      (вҲҖ C, Differentiable в„Ӯ (Z C)) вҲ§
      (вҲҖ C, вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, 1 < s.re вҶ’
        LSeriesSummable (fun n => (classIdealCount K C n : в„Ӯ)) s вҲ§
        Z C s = s * (s - 1) * Complex.ofReal |(NumberField.discr K : в„қ)| ^ (s / 2) *
          ((Real.pi : в„Ӯ) ^ (-s / 2) * Complex.Gamma (s / 2)) ^
            NumberField.InfinitePlace.nrRealPlaces K *
          ((2 : в„Ӯ) * ((2 * Real.pi : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) ^ (-s) * Complex.Gamma s) ^
            NumberField.InfinitePlace.nrComplexPlaces K *
          LSeries (fun n => (classIdealCount K C n : в„Ӯ)) s) вҲ§
      (вҲҖ C, вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, Z C (1 - s) = Z (dedekindDualClass K C) s) вҲ§
      (вҲҖ C, вҲғ B : в„қ, 0 < B вҲ§ вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, 2 вүӨ вҖ–sвҖ– вҶ’
        вҖ–Z C sвҖ– вүӨ Real.exp (B * вҖ–sвҖ– * Real.log вҖ–sвҖ–)) := by
  obtain вҹЁP, ПҒ, hk, hОө, hfвӮҖ, hgвӮҖ, hОӣвӮҖFE, hdecay, hMellвҹ© := heckeFEPair_exists K hОё
  -- The pole-clearing identity: away from `s вҲҲ {0, 1}` the entire
  -- candidate `s(sвҲ’1)В·ОӣвӮҖ(s/2) + 2ПҒ` is exactly `s(sвҲ’1)В·Оӣ(s/2)`.
  have key : вҲҖ C, вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, s вү  0 вҶ’ s вү  1 вҶ’
      s * (s - 1) * (P C).ОӣвӮҖ (s / 2) + 2 * ПҒ = s * (s - 1) * (P C).Оӣ (s / 2) := by
    intro C s hs0 hs1
    rw [(P C).ОӣвӮҖ_eq, hk C, hОө C, hfвӮҖ C, hgвӮҖ C, smul_eq_mul, smul_eq_mul]
    push_cast
    have h1 : s / 2 вү  0 := div_ne_zero hs0 two_ne_zero
    have h2 : (1 : в„Ӯ) / 2 - s / 2 вү  0 := by
      intro h
      apply hs1
      linear_combination -2 * h
    field_simp
    ring
  refine вҹЁfun C s => s * (s - 1) * (P C).ОӣвӮҖ (s / 2) + 2 * ПҒ,
    fun C => ?_, fun C s hs => ?_, fun C s => ?_, fun C => ?_вҹ©
  В· -- Entirety, from `WeakFEPair.differentiable_ОӣвӮҖ`.
    have h1 : Differentiable в„Ӯ (P C).ОӣвӮҖ := (P C).differentiable_ОӣвӮҖ
    fun_prop
  В· -- The `re s > 1` formula, through the Mellin identification.
    obtain вҹЁhsum, hОӣвҹ© := hMell C s hs
    have hs0 : s вү  0 := by rintro rfl; norm_num at hs
    have hs1 : s вү  1 := by rintro rfl; norm_num at hs
    refine вҹЁhsum, ?_вҹ©
    dsimp only
    rw [key C s hs0 hs1, hОӣ]
    ring
  В· -- The functional equation, from the `ОӣвӮҖ`-level one.
    have h2 : (1 - s) / 2 = 1 / 2 - s / 2 := by ring
    dsimp only
    rw [h2, hОӣвӮҖFE C (s / 2)]
    ring
  В· -- The order-one growth bound, from `weakFEPair_growth`.
    obtain вҹЁA, a, ha, hfd, hgdвҹ© := hdecay C
    obtain вҹЁB, hB, hboundвҹ© := weakFEPair_growth (P C) (hk C) A a ha hfd hgd
    refine вҹЁB, hB, fun s hs => ?_вҹ©
    have hs0 : s вү  0 := by rintro rfl; norm_num at hs
    have hs1 : s вү  1 := by rintro rfl; norm_num at hs
    dsimp only
    rw [key C s hs0 hs1]
    exact hbound s hs

/-- **Hecke's theorem, per-ideal-class thetaвҖ“Mellin core**
(DECOMPOSED 2026-07-24, assembly PROVEN): every ideal class `C` of `K`
has an entire `s(sвҲ’1)`-normalized completed partial zeta `Z C` вҖ” on
`re s > 1` equal to `s(sвҲ’1)В·|d_K|^{s/2}В·О“_в„қ(s)^{rвӮҒ}В·О“_в„Ӯ(s)^{rвӮӮ}`
times the (absolutely convergent, whence the bundled
`LSeriesSummable`) partial Dirichlet series of the class
(`classIdealCount`) вҖ” satisfying the functional equation
`Z C (1вҲ’s) = Z ([рқ”Ў]CвҒ»В№) s` (`dedekindDualClass`) and an order-one
growth bound off the disc `вҖ–sвҖ– < 2`.

The decomposition cuts the Neukirch VII В§В§3вҖ“5 route at its Poisson
core: the conclusion is verbatim that of
`heckeClassZeta_of_zlattice_theta` (the ideal-lattice, unit-domain and
`WeakFEPair`/Mellin machinery вҖ” assembly PROVEN above, over the
sorried leaves `heckeFEPair_exists`/`weakFEPair_growth`), whose sole
hypothesis
is verbatim the `n`-dimensional `ZLattice` Poisson-summation theta law
`zlattice_theta_transform` (sorried above, the pin's genuine gap) вҖ”
the assembly here plugs the one into the other, making the analytic
route and its two remaining frontiers mechanically explicit.

Historical intended-proof sketch (now distributed over the two
leaves' docstrings):

1. *Theta series of the class* (Neukirch VII В§3).  Choose an integral
   ideal `рқ”һ вҲҲ CвҒ»В№`; the integral ideals in `C` biject with the
   nonzero `рқ’Ә_K^Г—`-orbits on `рқ”һ` (`рқ”ҹ вҶҰ рқ”ҹрқ”һ = (a)`,
   `Nрқ”ҹ = |N_{K/в„ҡ}(a)|/Nрқ”һ`), so the completed partial zeta is an
   integral of the theta series of the lattice `рқ”һ вҠӮ K_в„қ = в„қ^{rвӮҒ} Г—
   в„Ӯ^{rвӮӮ}` (mathlib: `NumberField.mixedEmbedding` with its `ZLattice`
   structure on ideals,
   `Mathlib.NumberTheory.NumberField.CanonicalEmbedding.*`).  The
   transformation law of the theta series under `t вҶҰ 1/t` (Neukirch
   VII (3.6)) is Poisson summation on `рқ”һ` with trace-dual lattice
   `(рқ”һВ·рқ”Ў)вҒ»В№` (`differentIdeal`) вҖ” whence the class shift `[рқ”Ў]CвҒ»В№`;
   the pin has ONE-dimensional Poisson summation
   (`Mathlib.Analysis.Fourier.PoissonSummation`) and Gaussian
   self-duality
   (`Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.Gaussian.PoissonSummation`,
   `Mathlib.NumberTheory.ModularForms.JacobiTheta.TwoVariable`) вҖ” the
   `n`-dimensional `ZLattice` version is the genuine gap: the product
   structure of the Gaussian reduces the `в„ӨвҒҝ` case to `n`
   one-dimensional applications, and a general lattice is `BВ·в„ӨвҒҝ` for a
   basis `B`, handled by the change-of-variables formula for the
   Fourier transform.
2. *Unit-domain reduction and Mellin transform* (Neukirch VII В§5,
   (5.5)вҖ“(5.8)): integrating over a fundamental domain of the action
   of `рқ’Ә_K^Г—/Ој(K)` on the norm-one hypersurface of `K_в„қ^Г—` turns the
   completed partial zeta `Z(C, s)` into the Mellin transform of a
   theta integral `g_C(t)` with law `g_C(1/t) = t^{1/2}В·g_{C'}(t)`;
   instantiate mathlib's `WeakFEPair`
   (`Mathlib.NumberTheory.LSeries.AbstractFuncEq`, exactly as
   `Mathlib.NumberTheory.LSeries.HurwitzZetaEven` does): its main
   theorems yield the continuation of `Z(C, В·)` to `в„Ӯ вҲ– {0, 1}` with
   simple poles of known residue at `0` and `1`, the entirety of
   `s(sвҲ’1)В·Z(C, s)`, and the functional equation
   `Z(C, s) = Z(C', 1 вҲ’ s)`.  The absolute convergence of the partial
   series on `re s > 1` (the `LSeriesSummable` conjunct) falls out of
   the same Mellin analysis, or directly from the pin's per-class
   CesГ ro asymptotics `Ideal.tendsto_norm_le_and_mk_eq_div_atTop`
   via `LSeriesSummable_of_sum_norm_bigO`.
3. *`re s > 1` formula*: Neukirch VII В§4's computation of the
   archimedean Euler factors (`О“_в„қ(s) = ПҖ^{-s/2}О“(s/2)`,
   `О“_в„Ӯ(s) = 2(2ПҖ)^{-s}О“(s)`).
4. *Growth* (S. Lang, *Algebraic Number Theory*, XIII В§5): on
   `re s вүҘ 2`, termwise `вҖ–L(a_C, s)вҖ– вүӨ L(a_C, 2)` (nonnegative
   coefficients) and `вҖ–О“(s)вҖ– вүӨ О“(re s)` (integral representation)
   with the elementary `О“(x) вүӨ x^x = exp(x log x)`; on `re s вүӨ вҲ’1`
   reflect through the functional equation (`вҖ–1 вҲ’ sвҖ– вүӨ 1 + вҖ–sвҖ–`); on
   the strip `вҲ’1 вүӨ re s вүӨ 2` use the a priori bound
   `вҖ–Z C sвҖ– вүӨ вҖ–s(sвҲ’1)вҖ–В·(cвӮҖ + вҲ«_1^вҲһ ОёМғ(t)В·(t^{re s/2} + t^{(1вҲ’re s)/2})
   dt/t)`, bounded polynomially there by the Mellin representation of
   step 2 вҖ” or PhragmГ©nвҖ“LindelГ¶f
   (`Mathlib.Analysis.Complex.PhragmenLindelof.horizontal_strip`,
   already imported).

The official FLT project takes the downstream discriminant bound as a
standing axiom (`FLT.Assumptions.Odlyzko`); here Hecke's theorem is an
honest leaf. -/
theorem completedClassZeta_exists (K : Type*) [Field K] [NumberField K] :
    вҲғ Z : ClassGroup (NumberField.RingOfIntegers K) вҶ’ в„Ӯ вҶ’ в„Ӯ,
      (вҲҖ C, Differentiable в„Ӯ (Z C)) вҲ§
      (вҲҖ C, вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, 1 < s.re вҶ’
        LSeriesSummable (fun n => (classIdealCount K C n : в„Ӯ)) s вҲ§
        Z C s = s * (s - 1) * Complex.ofReal |(NumberField.discr K : в„қ)| ^ (s / 2) *
          ((Real.pi : в„Ӯ) ^ (-s / 2) * Complex.Gamma (s / 2)) ^
            NumberField.InfinitePlace.nrRealPlaces K *
          ((2 : в„Ӯ) * ((2 * Real.pi : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) ^ (-s) * Complex.Gamma s) ^
            NumberField.InfinitePlace.nrComplexPlaces K *
          LSeries (fun n => (classIdealCount K C n : в„Ӯ)) s) вҲ§
      (вҲҖ C, вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, Z C (1 - s) = Z (dedekindDualClass K C) s) вҲ§
      (вҲҖ C, вҲғ B : в„қ, 0 < B вҲ§ вҲҖ s : в„Ӯ, 2 вүӨ вҖ–sвҖ– вҶ’
        вҖ–Z C sвҖ– вүӨ Real.exp (B * вҖ–sвҖ– * Real.log вҖ–sвҖ–)) := by
  refine heckeClassZeta_of_zlattice_theta K ?_
  intro E _ _ _ _ _ L _ _ t ht
  exact zlattice_theta_transform L t ht

