/-- **The horizontal-edge functional of Poitou's contour**
(definition, 2026-07-24 вҖ” introduced in the decomposition of
`DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_sub_poitouEdge_tendsto_zero`): the
combined contribution of the two horizontal edges of the rectangle
`[вҲ’1/4, 5/4] Г— [вҲ’T, T]` to the counterclockwise contour integral of
`ОҰВ·Оҫ'/Оҫ`, with the `(2ПҖi)вҒ»В№` normalization of the residue theorem:

`H(T) = Re[(2ПҖi)вҒ»В№В·(вҲ«_{вҲ’1/4}^{5/4} (ОҰВ·Оҫ'/Оҫ)(Пғ вҲ’ iT) dПғ
вҲ’ вҲ«_{вҲ’1/4}^{5/4} (ОҰВ·Оҫ'/Оҫ)(Пғ + iT) dПғ)]`

вҖ” the bottom edge is traversed left-to-right and the top edge
right-to-left, whence the minus sign; on both edges `ds = dПғ`.
Together with the folded vertical-edge functional
`DedekindContinuation.poitouEdge` this exhausts the whole contour:
`DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_eq_poitouEdge_add_poitouHorizontal`
states the exact identity `S(T) = E(T) + H(T)` at every height
avoiding the zero ordinates, and Poitou's Proposition 1
(`DedekindContinuation.poitouHorizontal_gap_tendsto_zero`) kills `H`
along the good-height selections of
`DedekindContinuation.exists_goodHeight_gap`. -/
noncomputable def DedekindContinuation.poitouHorizontal {K : Type*} [Field K]
    [NumberField K] (pkg : DedekindContinuation K) (T : в„қ) : в„қ :=
  ((2 * (Real.pi : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)вҒ»В№ *
    ((вҲ« Пғ in (-(1 / 4) : в„қ)..(5 / 4),
        poitouPhi (Пғ - T * Complex.I) *
          (deriv pkg.xi (Пғ - T * Complex.I) / pkg.xi (Пғ - T * Complex.I))) -
      вҲ« Пғ in (-(1 / 4) : в„қ)..(5 / 4),
        poitouPhi (Пғ + T * Complex.I) *
          (deriv pkg.xi (Пғ + T * Complex.I) / pkg.xi (Пғ + T * Complex.I)))).re

/-- **Poitou's formula (1): the truncated zero sum equals the folded
vertical edge plus the horizontal edges вҖ” an exact identity at
ordinate-avoiding heights** (sorry node, stated 2026-07-24 вҖ” leaf
(bвӮҒбөў), the residue-theorem stage of the decomposition of
`DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_sub_poitouEdge_tendsto_zero`; Poitou
pp. 6-01вҖ“6-02, formula (1)).

Intended proof, verified against the page scans
`~/flt-sources/poitou-page-0*.png`:

1. *Residue theorem on `R = [вҲ’1/4, 5/4] Г— [вҲ’T, T]`.*  The pin has no
   argument principle, so manufacture it: the zeros of `Оҫ` in the
   closed rectangle are finitely many (`finite_truncation`) and ALL
   lie in the open strip `0 < re ПҒ < 1` with `|im ПҒ| < T` вҖ” `hbnd`
   excludes the line `re = 1` (in particular the point `1`, and
   `0 = 1 вҲ’ 1` via `funcEq`), `ne_zero_of_one_lt_re` excludes
   `re > 1`, the `funcEq` mirror excludes `re < 0`, and `hgood`
   excludes `|im ПҒ| = T`; on the strip `mult` IS `analyticOrderNatAt`
   by definition.  Divide the zeros out: by the isolated-zeros
   divided factorization (iterated `dslope` division
   `sub_smul_dslope_of_zero` with `Complex.differentiableOn_dslope`,
   exactly as in `sum_analyticOrderNatAt_le_of_frontier_norm_le`)
   the function
   `s вҶҰ ОҰ(s)В·(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(s) вҲ’ ОЈ_ПҒ mult(ПҒ)В·ОҰ(ПҒ)/(s вҲ’ ПҒ)` extends
   differentiably across every zero (`ОҰ = poitouPhi` is entire вҖ” the
   parameter-integral differentiability proved for
   `poitouPhi_differentiable` later in this file; manufacture a
   forward-placed brick or reorder).  Apply the pin's rectangle
   Cauchy theorem
   `Complex.integral_boundary_rect_eq_zero_of_differentiableOn` to it
   over `R`, and evaluate the elementary rectangle integrals
   `вҲ®_вҲӮR ds/(s вҲ’ ПҒ) = 2ПҖi` for interior `ПҒ` (same Cauchy theorem
   against a shrunk concentric rectangle, or directly).  Result:
   `(2ПҖi)вҒ»В№В·вҲ®_вҲӮR ОҰВ·Оҫ'/Оҫ = ОЈ_{mult ПҒ вү  0, |im ПҒ| вүӨ T} mult(ПҒ)В·ОҰ(ПҒ)`,
   the tsum being this finite sum by `finite_truncation` and
   `tsum_eq_sum`.
2. *Folding the left edge onto the right.*  `funcEq` differentiated
   gives `Оҫ'(1 вҲ’ s) = вҲ’Оҫ'(s)`, so `(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(1 вҲ’ s) = вҲ’(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(s)`
   wherever `Оҫ(s) вү  0`; and `ОҰ(1 вҲ’ s) = ОҰ(s)` (substitute `x вҶҰ вҲ’x`
   inside `poitouPhi`; `odlyzkoTestFn` is even).  Under `t вҶҰ вҲ’t` the
   left-edge integrand at `вҲ’1/4 + it` becomes MINUS the right-edge
   integrand at `5/4 + it` (`Оҫ(вҲ’1/4 + it) вү  0` because
   `Оҫ(5/4 вҲ’ it) вү  0` by `ne_zero_of_one_lt_re` and `funcEq`), and
   the left edge is traversed downward, so the two vertical edges
   contribute equally:
   `vertical = ПҖвҒ»В№В·вҲ«_{вҲ’T}^{T} (ОҰВ·Оҫ'/Оҫ)(5/4 + it) dt`.  Taking real
   parts of the whole identity (`Complex.re` passes through the
   integrals, `intervalIntegral` is `в„қ`-linear in the target) turns
   the vertical term into `DedekindContinuation.poitouEdge T`, the
   zero side into the stated tsum of `Re ОҰ(ПҒ)`, and the horizontal
   remainder into `DedekindContinuation.poitouHorizontal T`. -/
theorem DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_eq_poitouEdge_add_poitouHorizontal
    {K : Type*} [Field K] [NumberField K] (pkg : DedekindContinuation K)
    (hbnd : вҲҖ t : в„қ, pkg.xi (1 + t * Complex.I) вү  0)
    {T : в„қ} (hT : 0 < T)
    (hgood : вҲҖ ПҒ : в„Ӯ, pkg.mult ПҒ вү  0 вҶ’ |ПҒ.im| вү  T) :
    (вҲ‘' ПҒ : {ПҒ : в„Ӯ // pkg.mult ПҒ вү  0 вҲ§ |ПҒ.im| вүӨ T},
      (pkg.mult ПҒ.1 : в„қ) * (poitouPhi ПҒ.1).re) =
      pkg.poitouEdge T + pkg.poitouHorizontal T := by
  sorry

/-- **Good heights exist: a pigeonhole gap to the zero ordinates**
(sorry node, stated 2026-07-24 вҖ” leaf (bвӮҒбөўбөў) of the decomposition of
`DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_sub_poitouEdge_tendsto_zero`; the
