Intended proof: the ordinates `|im ПҒ|` of the zeros with
`|im ПҒ| вҲҲ (T вҲ’ 1, T + 2)` form a finite set (`finite_truncation` at
`T + 2`) of cardinality `N вүӨ 4В·CВ·log T` вҖ” each distinct ordinate is
witnessed by one zero of `mult вүҘ 1` (an injective choice of
representatives into a `Finset в„Ӯ`), and the two `hcount` windows
centred at `T` and at `T + 1` cover `(T вҲ’ 1, T + 2)`, with
`log (T + 1) вүӨ 2В·log T` for `T вүҘ 2`.  Among the `N + 1` equispaced
candidates `T + (2k + 1)/(2(N + 1))`, `k = 0, вҖҰ, N` (pairwise gaps
