`sum_analyticOrderNatAt_le_of_frontier_norm_le`) вҖ” bounds
`вҖ–(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(Пғ Вұ iВ·П„(T)) вҲ’ ОЈ_{near ПҒ} mult(ПҒ)/(s вҲ’ ПҒ)вҖ– = O(TВ·log T)` for
`Пғ вҲҲ [вҲ’1/4, 5/4]`; the near-zero partial fractions are
`O(log T В· log T/c) = O(logВІ T)` by `hcount` and the injected
ordinate gap `c/log T` (via `hbnd`, `funcEq` and
`ne_zero_of_one_lt_re` every zero met by the closed strip carries
`mult вү  0`, so the gap applies to every singularity near the
segment).  Meanwhile `вҖ–ОҰ(Пғ Вұ iВ·П„(T))вҖ– = O(1/TВІ)` uniformly in
`Пғ вҲҲ [вҲ’1/4, 5/4]`: two integrations by parts in `poitouPhi` against
the piecewise-`CВ№` compactly supported `poitouF` (kink terms at
`x вҲҲ {вҲ’6, 0, 6}` only).  The horizontal edges are
`O(TВ·log T + logВІ T)В·O(1/TВІ)В·(3/2) = O(log T/T) вҶ’ 0`. -/
theorem DedekindContinuation.poitouHorizontal_gap_tendsto_zero {K : Type*}
    [Field K] [NumberField K] (pkg : DedekindContinuation K)
    (hcount : вҲғ C : в„қ, 0 < C вҲ§ вҲҖ T : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’ вҲҖ s : Finset в„Ӯ,
      (вҲҖ ПҒ вҲҲ s, |(|ПҒ.im| - T)| вүӨ 1) вҶ’
      вҲ‘ ПҒ вҲҲ s, (pkg.mult ПҒ : в„қ) вүӨ C * Real.log T)
    (hbnd : вҲҖ t : в„қ, pkg.xi (1 + t * Complex.I) вү  0)
    {c : в„қ} (hc : 0 < c) (П„ : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ)
    (hП„ : вҲҖ T : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’ T вүӨ П„ T вҲ§ П„ T вүӨ T + 1 вҲ§
      вҲҖ ПҒ : в„Ӯ, pkg.mult ПҒ вү  0 вҶ’ c / Real.log T вүӨ |(|ПҒ.im| - П„ T)|) :
    Filter.Tendsto (fun T : в„қ => pkg.poitouHorizontal (П„ T))
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
  sorry

/-- **Bridging the zero sum from good heights to all heights** (sorry
node, stated 2026-07-24 вҖ” leaf (bвӮҒбөўбөҘ) of the decomposition of
`DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_sub_poitouEdge_tendsto_zero`; Poitou
p. 6-02, the reduction of formula (1) to good heights).  Moving the
truncation from `T` up to `П„(T) вҲҲ [T, T + 1]` changes the zero sum
exactly by the zeros with `T < |im ПҒ| вүӨ П„(T)`: at most `CВ·log T` of
them with multiplicity by `hcount` (they satisfy
`||im ПҒ| вҲ’ T| вүӨ 1`), each weighted by
`|Re ОҰ(ПҒ)| вүӨ вҖ–ОҰ(ПҒ)вҖ– = O(1/TВІ)` (two integrations by parts in
`poitouPhi`, uniform over the strip `0 < re ПҒ < 1` given by
`mult_mem_strip`), so the difference is `O(log T/TВІ) вҶ’ 0`.
Formally: both tsums are finite sums over subsets of the
`finite_truncation (T + 1)` truncation (`tsum_eq_sum` after
injecting the subtypes into its `Finset`), the difference collapses
to the sum over the annular finset
`{ПҒ : T < |im ПҒ| вүӨ П„(T)}`, and `hcount` against the `ОҰ`-decay bound
majorizes it by a null sequence. -/
theorem DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_bridge_tendsto_zero {K : Type*}
    [Field K] [NumberField K] (pkg : DedekindContinuation K)
    (hcount : вҲғ C : в„қ, 0 < C вҲ§ вҲҖ T : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’ вҲҖ s : Finset в„Ӯ,
      (вҲҖ ПҒ вҲҲ s, |(|ПҒ.im| - T)| вүӨ 1) вҶ’
      вҲ‘ ПҒ вҲҲ s, (pkg.mult ПҒ : в„қ) вүӨ C * Real.log T)
    (П„ : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ) (hП„ : вҲҖ T : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’ T вүӨ П„ T вҲ§ П„ T вүӨ T + 1) :
    Filter.Tendsto (fun T : в„қ =>
        (вҲ‘' ПҒ : {ПҒ : в„Ӯ // pkg.mult ПҒ вү  0 вҲ§ |ПҒ.im| вүӨ П„ T},
          (pkg.mult ПҒ.1 : в„қ) * (poitouPhi ПҒ.1).re) -
        вҲ‘' ПҒ : {ПҒ : в„Ӯ // pkg.mult ПҒ вү  0 вҲ§ |ПҒ.im| вүӨ T},
          (pkg.mult ПҒ.1 : в„қ) * (poitouPhi ПҒ.1).re)
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
  sorry

/-- **Bridging the folded vertical edge from good heights to all
heights** (sorry node, stated 2026-07-24 вҖ” leaf (bвӮҒбөҘ) of the
decomposition of
`DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_sub_poitouEdge_tendsto_zero`; Poitou
p. 6-02).  `poitouEdge (П„ T) вҲ’ poitouEdge T
= ПҖвҒ»В№В·(вҲ«_{T}^{П„ T} + вҲ«_{вҲ’П„ T}^{вҲ’T}) Re[(ОҰВ·Оҫ'/Оҫ)(5/4 + it)] dt` by
`intervalIntegral` additivity вҖ” the integrand is continuous on the
whole line `re s = 5/4`: `ne_zero_of_one_lt_re` keeps `Оҫ вү  0` there,
`differentiable` gives continuity of `Оҫ` and (via
`Differentiable.deriv` analyticity) of `Оҫ'`, and `poitouPhi` is a
continuous parameter integral.  On the line, two integrations by
parts give `вҖ–ОҰ(5/4 + it)вҖ– = O(1/tВІ)`, while
`(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(5/4 + it) = 1/s + 1/(sвҲ’1) + (log|d|)/2 + rвӮҒВ·(О“_в„қ'/О“_в„қ) +
rвӮӮВ·(О“_в„Ӯ'/О“_в„Ӯ) + (О¶_K'/О¶_K)` (log-derivative of `eq_of_one_lt_re`)
is `O(log t)` вҖ” the Dirichlet series `О¶_K'/О¶_K` is bounded on the
line by absolute convergence and the digamma factors grow
logarithmically (a crude `O(log t)`, or even `O(t)`, suffices
against the `1/tВІ` decay).  The bridging windows have length
`П„ T вҲ’ T вүӨ 1`, so the change is `O(log T/TВІ) вҶ’ 0`. -/
theorem DedekindContinuation.poitouEdge_bridge_tendsto_zero {K : Type*}
    [Field K] [NumberField K] (pkg : DedekindContinuation K) (П„ : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ)
    (hП„ : вҲҖ T : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’ T вүӨ П„ T вҲ§ П„ T вүӨ T + 1) :
    Filter.Tendsto (fun T : в„қ => pkg.poitouEdge (П„ T) - pkg.poitouEdge T)
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
  sorry

/-- **Poitou's formula (1) with vanishing horizontal edges: the
truncated zero sum equals the folded vertical edge in the limit**
(ASSEMBLED 2026-07-24 over the five stage leaves
`DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_eq_poitouEdge_add_poitouHorizontal`
(steps 1вҖ“2 below, the exact identity at ordinate-avoiding heights),
`DedekindContinuation.exists_goodHeight_gap` and
`DedekindContinuation.poitouHorizontal_gap_tendsto_zero` (step 3,
Proposition 1), and `DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_bridge_tendsto_zero`
with `DedekindContinuation.poitouEdge_bridge_tendsto_zero` (step 4,
the good-height-to-all-heights bridging); originally leaf (bвӮҒ), the
residue-theorem stage of the decomposition of
`DedekindContinuation.weil_explicit_formula_F`; Poitou pp. 6-01вҖ“6-02,
formula (1) and Proposition 1.  The window count is
dependency-injected as `hcount` and the boundary nonvanishing as
`hbnd` so that the leaves `DedekindContinuation.zero_count_window`
and `DedekindContinuation.xi_ne_zero_of_re_eq_one` stay in the
used-constant cone while the stage leaves are open.

The assembly: `exists_goodHeight_gap` yields `c > 0` and (through
choice) a selection `П„` with `П„(T) вҲҲ [T, T + 1]` at ordinate gap
`вүҘ c/log T`; the gap is positive, so the exact identity applies at
`П„(T)` and splits `S(T) вҲ’ E(T)` as
`вҲ’(S(П„(T)) вҲ’ S(T)) + H(П„(T)) + (E(П„(T)) вҲ’ E(T))`, a sum of three
null sequences.  Proof route of the leaves, verified against the
page scans `~/flt-sources/poitou-page-0*.png`:

1. *Residue theorem at a fixed good height.*  For `T'` avoiding all
   zero ordinates, on `R = [вҲ’1/4, 5/4] Г— [вҲ’T', T']`:
   `(2ПҖi)вҒ»В№ вҲ®_вҲӮR ОҰВ·Оҫ'/Оҫ = ОЈ_{ПҒ вҲҲ R} mult(ПҒ)В·ОҰ(ПҒ)`.  Mathlib has no
   residue theorem, but the pin's rectangle Cauchy theorem
   `Complex.integral_boundary_rect_eq_zero_of_differentiableOn`
   applies to `s вҶҰ ОҰ(s)В·(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(s) вҲ’ ОЈ_{ПҒ вҲҲ R} mult(ПҒ)В·ОҰ(ПҒ)/(s вҲ’ ПҒ)`
   after the finitely many zeros (`finite_truncation`) are divided
   out by the local factorization `Оҫ = (В· вҲ’ ПҒ)^{mult ПҒ} вҖў g`,
   `g ПҒ вү  0`, of `Mathlib.Analysis.Analytic.IsolatedZeros`/`Order`
   (this difference extends differentiably across each `ПҒ`), plus
   the elementary rectangle integral
   `вҲ®_вҲӮR ds/(s вҲ’ ПҒ) = 2ПҖi` for `ПҒ` interior (computable by the same
   Cauchy theorem against a concentric circle, or directly).  `hbnd`
   with `ne_zero_of_one_lt_re`, `funcEq` and `conj_symm` puts every
   zero in the open strip, so the residue sum is exactly the `mult`
   sum and `0, 1` contribute nothing (`Оҫ(0) = Оҫ(1) вү  0` вҖ” note
   `funcEq` at `s = 1` gives `Оҫ(0) = Оҫ(1)`, and `hbnd 0` gives
   `Оҫ(1) вү  0`).
2. *Folding.*  `funcEq` differentiates to
   `(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(1 вҲ’ s) = вҲ’(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(s)` off the zeros, and `ОҰ(1 вҲ’ s) = ОҰ(s)`
   (substitute `x вҶҰ вҲ’x` in `poitouPhi`, `F` even), so the left edge
   equals the right edge and `(2ПҖi)вҒ»В№ вҲ® = ПҖвҒ»В№ вҲ«_{вҲ’T'}^{T'} Re[вҖҰ] dt
   + horizontal edges` вҖ” realness of the folded edge by `conj_symm`.
   This is `DedekindContinuation.poitouEdge T'`.
3. *Proposition 1: horizontal edges vanish through good heights.*
   `hcount` gives `вүӨ CВ·log T` zeros with ordinate in `[T, T+1]`, so
   some height `T' вҲҲ [T, T+1]` has distance `вүҘ (2CВ·log T)вҒ»В№` to
   every zero ordinate.  On the disc `|s вҲ’ (1/2 + iT')| вүӨ 6`, the
   pin's `Complex.borelCaratheodory` (present:
   `Mathlib.Analysis.Complex.BorelCaratheodory`) applied to
   `log(Оҫ/((sвҲ’ПҒвӮҒ)^{mвӮҒ}вӢҜ))` вҖ” equivalently the standard partial
   fraction bound manufactured from `growth`, `hcount` and the
   Schwarz-type estimates of that file вҖ” yields
   `|(Оҫ'/Оҫ)(Пғ + iT')| = O(logВІ T)` uniformly for
   `Пғ вҲҲ [вҲ’1/4, 5/4]`, while `вҖ–ОҰ(Пғ + iT')вҖ– = O(1/T'ВІ)` uniformly on
   the strip (two integrations by parts in `poitouPhi` against the
   compactly supported `F` with `F'` of bounded variation).  The
   horizontal edges are `O(logВІ T/TВІ) вҶ’ 0`.
4. *Bridging from good heights to all heights.*  For
   `T вүӨ S < T + 2` the zero sum changes by
   `O(log T)В·sup_{|imПҒ|вүҘT}вҖ–ОҰ(ПҒ)вҖ– = O(log T/TВІ)` (by `hcount` and
   step 3's decay of `ОҰ` on the strip), and `poitouEdge` changes by
   `вҲ«_{T}^{S} O(log t/tВІ) dt вҶ’ 0` (on `re s = 5/4` the series
   `(Оҫ'/Оҫ)` is `O(1)` by `eq_of_one_lt_re`-side estimates, or crudely
   `O(log t)` again), so the difference tends to `0` along ALL
   `T вҶ’ вҲһ`, as stated. -/
theorem DedekindContinuation.zero_sum_sub_poitouEdge_tendsto_zero {K : Type*}
    [Field K] [NumberField K] (pkg : DedekindContinuation K)
    (hcount : вҲғ C : в„қ, 0 < C вҲ§ вҲҖ T : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’ вҲҖ s : Finset в„Ӯ,
      (вҲҖ ПҒ вҲҲ s, |(|ПҒ.im| - T)| вүӨ 1) вҶ’
      вҲ‘ ПҒ вҲҲ s, (pkg.mult ПҒ : в„қ) вүӨ C * Real.log T)
    (hbnd : вҲҖ t : в„қ, pkg.xi (1 + t * Complex.I) вү  0) :
    Filter.Tendsto (fun T : в„қ =>
        (вҲ‘' ПҒ : {ПҒ : в„Ӯ // pkg.mult ПҒ вү  0 вҲ§ |ПҒ.im| вүӨ T},
          (pkg.mult ПҒ.1 : в„қ) * (poitouPhi ПҒ.1).re) - pkg.poitouEdge T)
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
  obtain вҹЁc, hc, hgapвҹ© := pkg.exists_goodHeight_gap hcount
  have hsel : вҲҖ T : в„қ, вҲғ T' : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’ T вүӨ T' вҲ§ T' вүӨ T + 1 вҲ§
      вҲҖ ПҒ : в„Ӯ, pkg.mult ПҒ вү  0 вҶ’ c / Real.log T вүӨ |(|ПҒ.im| - T')| := by
    intro T
    by_cases hT : 2 вүӨ T
    В· obtain вҹЁT', hT'вҹ© := hgap T hT
      exact вҹЁT', fun _ => hT'вҹ©
    В· exact вҹЁT, fun h => absurd h hTвҹ©
  choose П„ hП„ using hsel
  have hП„' : вҲҖ T : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’ T вүӨ П„ T вҲ§ П„ T вүӨ T + 1 :=
    fun T hT => вҹЁ(hП„ T hT).1, (hП„ T hT).2.1вҹ©
  have hident : вҲҖ T : в„қ, 2 вүӨ T вҶ’
      (вҲ‘' ПҒ : {ПҒ : в„Ӯ // pkg.mult ПҒ вү  0 вҲ§ |ПҒ.im| вүӨ П„ T},
        (pkg.mult ПҒ.1 : в„қ) * (poitouPhi ПҒ.1).re) =
      pkg.poitouEdge (П„ T) + pkg.poitouHorizontal (П„ T) := by
    intro T hT
    obtain вҹЁh1, -, h3вҹ© := hП„ T hT
    refine pkg.zero_sum_eq_poitouEdge_add_poitouHorizontal hbnd
      (lt_of_lt_of_le (by linarith) h1) ?_
    intro ПҒ hПҒ heq
    have hg := h3 ПҒ hПҒ
    rw [heq, sub_self, abs_zero] at hg
    have hpos : 0 < c / Real.log T := div_pos hc (Real.log_pos (by linarith))
    linarith
  have hH := pkg.poitouHorizontal_gap_tendsto_zero hcount hbnd hc П„ hП„
  have hS := pkg.zero_sum_bridge_tendsto_zero hcount П„ hП„'
  have hE := pkg.poitouEdge_bridge_tendsto_zero П„ hП„'
  have hcomb := (hS.neg.add hH).add hE
  rw [neg_zero, zero_add, add_zero] at hcomb
  refine Filter.Tendsto.congr' ?_ hcomb
  filter_upwards [Filter.eventually_ge_atTop (2 : в„қ)] with T hT
  simp only [hident T hT]
  ring

/-- **The pole-pair edge functional** (definition, 2026-07-24 вҖ”
introduced in the decomposition of
`DedekindContinuation.poitouEdge_tendsto`): the analogue of
`DedekindContinuation.poitouEdge` with the elementary pole pair
`h(s) = 1/s + 1/(sвҲ’1)` вҖ” the log-derivative of the normalizing
factor `s(sвҲ’1)` of `Оҫ` вҖ” in place of `Оҫ'/Оҫ`.  `h` has the same odd
symmetry `h(1 вҲ’ s) = вҲ’h(s)` under the functional-equation
substitution as `Оҫ'/Оҫ` itself, which is why the same folded
right-edge form captures its whole rectangle contour.  Note
`(5/4 + it).re = 5/4`, so neither denominator vanishes on the
line. -/
noncomputable def poitouPoleEdge (T : в„қ) : в„қ :=
  Real.piвҒ»В№ * вҲ« t in (-T)..T,
    (poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) *
      (1 / (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) + 1 / (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I - 1))).re

section PoitouPoleEdgeFourier

open MeasureTheory Filter Set Complex
open scoped FourierTransform Convolution

/-- **The time-side profile of `ОҰ` on the line `Re s = 5/4`**
(introduced 2026-07-24 for the proof of `poitouPoleEdge_tendsto`):
`G(x) = F(x)В·e^{3x/4}` with `F = poitouF`, so that
`ОҰ(5/4 + it) = вҲ« G(x)В·e^{itx} dx` (`poitouPhi_line_eq`) вҖ” i.e. `G` is
the inverse Fourier profile of the edge restriction of `ОҰ`.  It is
continuous with support in `[-6, 6]`. -/
noncomputable def poitouG (x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ := ((poitouF x * Real.exp (3 / 4 * x) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)

/-- **Continuity of `poitouF`** (PROVEN 2026-07-24): quotient of the
continuous FejГ©r kernel by the positive `cosh`. -/
theorem continuous_poitouF : Continuous poitouF := by
  apply Continuous.div
  В· unfold odlyzkoTestFn; fun_prop
  В· fun_prop
  В· exact fun x => (Real.cosh_pos _).ne'

/-- **Continuity of `poitouG`** (PROVEN 2026-07-24). -/
theorem continuous_poitouG : Continuous poitouG := by
  refine Complex.continuous_ofReal.comp (continuous_poitouF.mul ?_)
  fun_prop

/-- **`poitouG` vanishes beyond the FejГ©r support `[-6, 6]`**
(PROVEN 2026-07-24). -/
theorem poitouG_eq_zero {x : в„қ} (hx : 6 вүӨ |x|) : poitouG x = 0 := by
  have h : odlyzkoTestFn x = 0 := by
    rw [odlyzkoTestFn, max_eq_right]
    have : (6:в„қ) вүӨ |x| := hx
    nlinarith [this]
  rw [poitouG, poitouF, h, zero_div, zero_mul, Complex.ofReal_zero]

/-- **`poitouG` has compact support** (PROVEN 2026-07-24). -/
theorem poitouG_hasCompactSupport : HasCompactSupport poitouG := by
  apply HasCompactSupport.intro (isCompact_Icc (a := (-6:в„қ)) (b := 6))
  intro x hx
  apply poitouG_eq_zero
  simp only [Set.mem_Icc, not_and_or, not_le] at hx
  rcases hx with h | h
  В· exact le_abs.2 (Or.inr (by linarith))
  В· exact le_abs.2 (Or.inl h.le)

/-- **`poitouG` is integrable** (PROVEN 2026-07-24): continuous with
compact support. -/
theorem poitouG_integrable : Integrable poitouG :=
  continuous_poitouG.integrable_of_hasCompactSupport poitouG_hasCompactSupport

/-- **`ОҰ` on the line `Re s = 5/4` as a Fourier-type integral of
`poitouG`** (PROVEN 2026-07-24): splitting
`e^{(3/4 + it)x} = e^{3x/4}В·e^{itx}` in the defining integral of
`poitouPhi`. -/
theorem poitouPhi_line_eq (t : в„қ) :
    poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) =
      вҲ« x : в„қ, poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) := by
  rw [poitouPhi]
  have h : вҲҖ x : в„қ, ((odlyzkoTestFn x / Real.cosh (x / 2) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) *
      Complex.exp ((5 / 4 + t * Complex.I - 1 / 2) * (x : в„Ӯ)) =
      poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) := by
    intro x
    rw [show ((5 / 4 + t * Complex.I - 1 / 2) * (x : в„Ӯ)) =
        ((3 / 4 * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) + ((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I by push_cast; ring,
      Complex.exp_add, poitouG, poitouF, вҶҗ Complex.ofReal_exp]
    push_cast
    ring
  simp_rw [h]

/-- **The Fourier transform of `poitouG` is `ОҰ` on the line**
(PROVEN 2026-07-24): with mathlib's `2ПҖ`-in-the-exponent convention,
`рқ“• poitouG Оҫ = ОҰ(5/4 - 2ПҖОҫВ·i)`. -/
theorem fourier_poitouG (Оҫ : в„қ) :
    рқ“• poitouG Оҫ = poitouPhi (5 / 4 + ((-(2 * Real.pi * Оҫ) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) := by
  rw [Real.fourier_real_eq_integral_exp_smul, poitouPhi_line_eq]
  have h : вҲҖ v : в„қ, Complex.exp (((-2 * Real.pi * v * Оҫ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) вҖў poitouG v
      = poitouG v * Complex.exp (((-(2 * Real.pi * Оҫ) * v : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) := by
    intro v
    rw [smul_eq_mul, mul_comm]
    congr 2
    push_cast
    ring
  simp_rw [h]

/-- **The one-sided exponential kernel `e^{ay}В·1_{y<0}`**
(introduced 2026-07-24 for the proof of `poitouPoleEdge_tendsto`): the
time-side profile of the pole factor `1/(a + it)` вҖ” its Fourier
transform is `1/(a - 2ПҖОҫВ·i)` (`fourier_expKernel`). -/
noncomputable def expKernel (a : в„қ) : в„қ вҶ’ в„Ӯ :=
  Set.indicator (Set.Iio (0 : в„қ)) fun y => Complex.exp (((a * y : в„қ) : в„Ӯ))

/-- **Integrability of `e^{zy}` on `(-вҲһ, 0]` for `Re z > 0`**
(PROVEN 2026-07-24; generic helper, reusable for one-sided Laplace
kernels). -/
theorem integrableOn_cexp_mul_Iic {z : в„Ӯ} (hz : 0 < z.re) :
    IntegrableOn (fun y : в„қ => Complex.exp (z * y)) (Set.Iic (0 : в„қ)) := by
  have h1 : IntegrableOn (fun u : в„қ => Real.exp (-z.re * u)) (Set.Ici (-(0:в„қ))) := by
    rw [neg_zero, integrableOn_Ici_iff_integrableOn_Ioi]
    exact exp_neg_integrableOn_Ioi 0 hz
  have h2 : IntegrableOn (fun y : в„қ => Real.exp (z.re * y)) (Set.Iic (0:в„қ)) := by
    refine h1.comp_neg_Iic.congr_fun (fun y _ => ?_) measurableSet_Iic
    simp
  refine h2.mono' ?_ ?_
  В· exact (Complex.continuous_exp.comp (by fun_prop)).aestronglyMeasurable
  В· refine Filter.Eventually.of_forall fun y => ?_
    rw [Complex.norm_exp]
    simp [Complex.mul_re]

/-- **Integrability of the one-sided exponential kernel**
(PROVEN 2026-07-24). -/
theorem expKernel_integrable {a : в„қ} (ha : 0 < a) : Integrable (expKernel a) := by
  rw [expKernel, integrable_indicator_iff measurableSet_Iio]
  have h := integrableOn_cexp_mul_Iic (z := (a : в„Ӯ)) (by simpa using ha)
  refine (h.mono_set Iio_subset_Iic_self).congr_fun (fun y _ => ?_) measurableSet_Iio
  push_cast
  ring_nf

/-- **`вҲ«_{-вҲһ}^0 e^{zy} dy = 1/z` for `Re z > 0`** (PROVEN 2026-07-24;
generic helper, reusable for one-sided Laplace kernels): improper
fundamental theorem of calculus on `Iic` with antiderivative
`e^{zy}/z` vanishing at `-вҲһ`. -/
theorem integral_cexp_mul_Iic {z : в„Ӯ} (hz : 0 < z.re) :
    вҲ« y in Set.Iic (0:в„қ), Complex.exp (z * y) = 1 / z := by
  have hz0 : z вү  0 := fun h => by simp [h] at hz
  have hder : вҲҖ y вҲҲ Set.Iio (0:в„қ),
      HasDerivAt (fun y : в„қ => Complex.exp (z * y) / z) (Complex.exp (z * y)) y := by
    intro y _
    have h1 : HasDerivAt (fun y : в„қ => z * (y : в„Ӯ)) z y := by
      simpa using (Complex.ofRealCLM.hasDerivAt (x := y)).const_mul z
    have h2 := h1.cexp.div_const z
    simpa [mul_div_cancel_rightвӮҖ _ hz0] using h2
  have htends : Tendsto (fun y : в„қ => Complex.exp (z * y) / z) atBot (nhds 0) := by
    rw [tendsto_zero_iff_norm_tendsto_zero]
    have hn : вҲҖ y : в„қ, вҖ–Complex.exp (z * y) / zвҖ– = Real.exp (z.re * y) / вҖ–zвҖ– := by
      intro y
      rw [norm_div, Complex.norm_exp]
      congr 2
      simp [Complex.mul_re]
    simp_rw [hn]
    have h3 : Tendsto (fun y : в„қ => z.re * y) atBot atBot :=
      Tendsto.const_mul_atBot hz tendsto_id
    simpa using (Real.tendsto_exp_atBot.comp h3).div_const вҖ–zвҖ–
  have hcont : ContinuousWithinAt (fun y : в„қ => Complex.exp (z * y) / z)
      (Set.Iic (0:в„қ)) 0 := by
    refine Continuous.continuousWithinAt ?_
    fun_prop
  have h := integral_Iic_of_hasDerivAt_of_tendsto hcont hder
    (integrableOn_cexp_mul_Iic hz) htends
  simpa using h

/-- **The Fourier transform of the one-sided exponential kernel is the
pole factor** (PROVEN 2026-07-24): `рқ“• (expKernel a) Оҫ = 1/(a - 2ПҖОҫВ·i)`,
written in the `a + ti` shape at `t = -2ПҖОҫ` to match
`fourier_poitouG`. -/
theorem fourier_expKernel {a : в„қ} (ha : 0 < a) (Оҫ : в„қ) :
    рқ“• (expKernel a) Оҫ = 1 / ((a : в„Ӯ) + ((-(2 * Real.pi * Оҫ) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) := by
  set z : в„Ӯ := (a : в„Ӯ) + ((-(2 * Real.pi * Оҫ) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I with hzdef
  have hzre : 0 < z.re := by
    rw [hzdef]
    simpa using ha
  rw [Real.fourier_real_eq_integral_exp_smul]
  have h : вҲҖ v : в„қ, Complex.exp (((-2 * Real.pi * v * Оҫ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) вҖў expKernel a v
      = Set.indicator (Set.Iio (0:в„қ)) (fun y => Complex.exp (z * y)) v := by
    intro v
    rw [smul_eq_mul, expKernel]
    by_cases hv : v вҲҲ Set.Iio (0:в„қ)
    В· rw [Set.indicator_of_mem hv, Set.indicator_of_mem hv, вҶҗ Complex.exp_add]
      congr 1
      rw [hzdef]
      push_cast
      ring
    В· rw [Set.indicator_of_notMem hv, Set.indicator_of_notMem hv, mul_zero]
  simp_rw [h]
  rw [integral_indicator measurableSet_Iio, setIntegral_congr_set Iio_ae_eq_Iic,
    integral_cexp_mul_Iic hzre]

/-- **The single-pole line integral by Fourier inversion**
(PROVEN 2026-07-24; the crux of `poitouPoleEdge_tendsto`): for `a > 0`,
`вҲ«_в„қ ОҰ(5/4 + it)/(a + it) dt = 2ПҖ вҲ«_0^вҲһ e^{-au}В·G(u) du`.  Proof: the
convolution `w = expKernel a вӢҶ poitouG` is integrable and continuous,
its Fourier transform is the pointwise product
`Оҫ вҶҰ ОҰ(5/4 - 2ПҖОҫi)/(a - 2ПҖОҫi)` (`Real.fourier_mul_convolution_eq` with
`fourier_expKernel` and `fourier_poitouG`), which is integrable by the
hypothesis after the linear change of variables `t = -2ПҖОҫ`; Fourier
inversion (`Integrable.fourierInv_fourier_eq`) at `0` then evaluates
`вҲ« рқ“• w = w 0`, and `w 0 = вҲ«_0^вҲһ e^{-au}В·G(u) du` by unfolding the
convolution over the negative half-line. -/
theorem integral_poitouPhi_line_div {a : в„қ} (ha : 0 < a)
    (hInt : Integrable fun t : в„қ =>
      poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I)) :
    (вҲ« t : в„қ, poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I))
      = (2 * Real.pi) вҖў вҲ« u in Set.Ioi (0:в„қ),
          Complex.exp (((-(a * u) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)) * poitouG u := by
  classical
  set w : в„қ вҶ’ в„Ӯ := expKernel a вӢҶ[ContinuousLinearMap.mul в„Ӯ в„Ӯ] poitouG with hw
  have hОә : Integrable (expKernel a) := expKernel_integrable ha
  have hwInt : Integrable w := hОә.integrable_convolution (ContinuousLinearMap.mul в„Ӯ в„Ӯ)
    poitouG_integrable
  have hwCont : Continuous w := poitouG_hasCompactSupport.continuous_convolution_right
    (ContinuousLinearMap.mul в„Ӯ в„Ӯ) hОә.locallyIntegrable continuous_poitouG
  have hFw : вҲҖ Оҫ : в„қ, рқ“• w Оҫ =
      poitouPhi (5 / 4 + ((-(2 * Real.pi * Оҫ) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) /
        ((a : в„Ӯ) + ((-(2 * Real.pi * Оҫ) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) := by
    intro Оҫ
    rw [hw, Real.fourier_mul_convolution_eq hОә poitouG_integrable, fourier_expKernel ha,
      fourier_poitouG, one_div_mul_eq_div]
  have hFwInt : Integrable (рқ“• w) := by
    have hne : (-(2 * Real.pi)) вү  (0:в„қ) := by
      simp [Real.pi_ne_zero]
    have h1 : Integrable fun Оҫ : в„қ =>
        poitouPhi (5 / 4 + (((-(2 * Real.pi)) * Оҫ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) /
          ((a : в„Ӯ) + (((-(2 * Real.pi)) * Оҫ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) :=
      hInt.comp_mul_left' hne
    refine h1.congr (Filter.Eventually.of_forall fun Оҫ => ?_)
    rw [hFw Оҫ]
    simp only [neg_mul]
  have hinv : рқ“•вҒ» (рқ“• w) 0 = w 0 := hwInt.fourierInv_fourier_eq hFwInt hwCont.continuousAt
  have hL : рқ“•вҒ» (рқ“• w) 0 = вҲ« Оҫ : в„қ, рқ“• w Оҫ := by
    rw [Real.fourierInv_eq_fourier_neg, neg_zero, Real.fourier_real_eq]
    simp
  have hchange : (вҲ« Оҫ : в„қ, рқ“• w Оҫ) = |((-(2 * Real.pi))вҒ»В№)| вҖў
      вҲ« t : в„қ, poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I) := by
    rw [show (fun Оҫ : в„қ => рқ“• w Оҫ) = fun Оҫ : в„қ =>
        (fun t : в„қ => poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I))
          ((-(2 * Real.pi)) * Оҫ) from funext fun Оҫ => by
        rw [hFw Оҫ]; push_cast; simp only [neg_mul]]
    exact MeasureTheory.Measure.integral_comp_mul_left
      (fun t : в„қ => poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I))
      (-(2 * Real.pi))
  have habs : |((-(2 * Real.pi))вҒ»В№)| = (2 * Real.pi)вҒ»В№ := by
    rw [abs_inv, abs_neg, abs_of_pos (by positivity)]
  have hw0 : w 0 = вҲ« u in Set.Ioi (0:в„қ),
      Complex.exp (((-(a * u) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)) * poitouG u := by
    rw [hw, convolution_def]
    simp only [ContinuousLinearMap.mul_apply', zero_sub]
    rw [show (fun t : в„қ => expKernel a t * poitouG (-t)) =
        Set.indicator (Set.Iio (0:в„қ))
          (fun t => Complex.exp (((a * t : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)) * poitouG (-t)) from funext fun t => by
        rw [expKernel]
        by_cases h : t вҲҲ Set.Iio (0:в„қ) <;> simp [h]]
    rw [integral_indicator measurableSet_Iio]
    have hni := integral_comp_neg_Ioi (0:в„қ)
      (fun t => Complex.exp (((a * t : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)) * poitouG (-t))
    rw [neg_zero] at hni
    rw [setIntegral_congr_set Iio_ae_eq_Iic, вҶҗ hni]
    refine setIntegral_congr_fun measurableSet_Ioi fun u _ => ?_
    rw [neg_neg]
    congr 2
    push_cast
    ring
  have hkey : (2 * Real.pi)вҒ»В№ вҖў
      (вҲ« t : в„қ, poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I)) = w 0 := by
    rw [вҶҗ habs, вҶҗ hchange, вҶҗ hL, hinv]
  have h2ПҖ : (0:в„қ) < 2 * Real.pi := by positivity
  calc (вҲ« t : в„қ, poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I))
      = ((2 * Real.pi) * (2 * Real.pi)вҒ»В№) вҖў
        (вҲ« t : в„қ, poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I)) := by
        rw [mul_inv_cancelвӮҖ h2ПҖ.ne', one_smul]
    _ = (2 * Real.pi) вҖў ((2 * Real.pi)вҒ»В№ вҖў
        (вҲ« t : в„қ, poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) / ((a : в„Ӯ) + t * Complex.I))) := by
        rw [mul_smul]
    _ = (2 * Real.pi) вҖў w 0 := by rw [hkey]
    _ = (2 * Real.pi) вҖў вҲ« u in Set.Ioi (0:в„қ),
          Complex.exp (((-(a * u) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)) * poitouG u := by rw [hw0]

/-- **The trivial `LВ№` bound of `ОҰ` on the line** (PROVEN 2026-07-24):
`вҖ–ОҰ(5/4 + it)вҖ– вүӨ вҖ–GвҖ–вӮҒ` uniformly in `t`. -/
theorem poitouPhi_line_norm_le_const (t : в„қ) :
    вҖ–poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I)вҖ– вүӨ вҲ« x : в„қ, вҖ–poitouG xвҖ– := by
  rw [poitouPhi_line_eq]
  refine (norm_integral_le_integral_norm _).trans (le_of_eq ?_)
  refine integral_congr_ae (Filter.Eventually.of_forall fun x => ?_)
  show вҖ–poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)вҖ– = вҖ–poitouG xвҖ–
  rw [norm_mul, Complex.norm_exp_ofReal_mul_I, mul_one]

/-- **Continuity of `ОҰ` along the line `Re s = 5/4`**
(PROVEN 2026-07-24): via `fourier_poitouG`, the map is the Fourier
transform of the integrable `poitouG` reparametrized by
`t вҶҰ -t/(2ПҖ)`, and Fourier transforms of integrable functions are
continuous. -/
theorem poitouPhi_line_continuous :
    Continuous fun t : в„қ => poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) := by
  have h1 : Continuous (рқ“• poitouG) :=
    VectorFourier.fourierIntegral_continuous Real.continuous_fourierChar
      (innerSL в„қ).continuousвӮӮ poitouG_integrable
  have h2 : (fun t : в„қ => poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I)) =
      fun t : в„қ => рқ“• poitouG (-(t / (2 * Real.pi))) := by
    funext t
    have hpi : -(2 * Real.pi * (-(t / (2 * Real.pi)))) = t := by
      field_simp
    rw [fourier_poitouG, hpi]
  rw [h2]
  exact h1.comp (by fun_prop)

/-- **The `1/|t|` decay of `ОҰ` on the line `Re s = 5/4`**
(PROVEN 2026-07-24): one integration by parts against the oscillation
`e^{itx}`, performed separately on `[-6, 0]` and `[0, 6]` where the
FejГ©r profile is affine (the smooth models `(1 Вұ x/6)В·e^{3x/4}/cosh(x/2)`
agree with `poitouG` there); the boundary terms cancel вҖ” the interface
values at `0` are both `1`, the outer endpoints vanish вҖ” leaving
`ОҰ = -(вҲ« rвӮҒ'В·v + вҲ« rвӮӮ'В·v)` with `вҖ–vвҖ– = 1/|t|`, whence the bound with
`M = вҲ«_{-6}^0 |rвӮҒ'| + вҲ«_0^6 |rвӮӮ'|`. -/
theorem poitouPhi_line_decay : вҲғ M : в„қ, 0 вүӨ M вҲ§ вҲҖ t : в„қ, t вү  0 вҶ’
    вҖ–poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I)вҖ– вүӨ M / |t| := by
  classical
  set q : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ := fun x => Real.exp (3 / 4 * x) / Real.cosh (x / 2) with hq
  set qd : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ := fun x =>
    (Real.exp (3 / 4 * x) * (3 / 4) * Real.cosh (x / 2) -
      Real.exp (3 / 4 * x) * (Real.sinh (x / 2) * (1 / 2))) / Real.cosh (x / 2) ^ 2 with hqd
  have hqder : вҲҖ x : в„қ, HasDerivAt q (qd x) x := by
    intro x
    have he : HasDerivAt (fun y : в„қ => Real.exp (3 / 4 * y))
        (Real.exp (3 / 4 * x) * (3 / 4)) x := by
      simpa using ((hasDerivAt_id x).const_mul (3 / 4 : в„қ)).exp
    have hhalf : HasDerivAt (fun y : в„қ => y / 2) ((1 : в„қ) / 2) x :=
      (hasDerivAt_id x).div_const 2
    have hc : HasDerivAt (fun y : в„қ => Real.cosh (y / 2)) (Real.sinh (x / 2) * (1 / 2)) x := by
      simpa using hhalf.cosh
    exact he.div hc (Real.cosh_pos _).ne'
  set rdвӮҒ : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ := fun x => 1 / 6 * q x + (1 + x / 6) * qd x with hrdвӮҒ
  set rdвӮӮ : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ := fun x => -(1 / 6) * q x + (1 - x / 6) * qd x with hrdвӮӮ
  have hrвӮҒder : вҲҖ x : в„қ, HasDerivAt (fun y : в„қ => (1 + y / 6) * q y) (rdвӮҒ x) x := by
    intro x
    exact (((hasDerivAt_id x).div_const (6 : в„қ)).const_add 1).mul (hqder x)
  have hrвӮӮder : вҲҖ x : в„қ, HasDerivAt (fun y : в„қ => (1 - y / 6) * q y) (rdвӮӮ x) x := by
    intro x
    exact (((hasDerivAt_id x).div_const (6 : в„қ)).const_sub 1).mul (hqder x)
  have hqcont : Continuous q := by
    refine Continuous.div (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop) fun x => (Real.cosh_pos _).ne'
  have hqdcont : Continuous qd := by
    refine Continuous.div (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop)
      fun x => pow_ne_zero _ (Real.cosh_pos _).ne'
  have hrdвӮҒcont : Continuous rdвӮҒ :=
    (hqcont.const_mul _).add
      ((continuous_const.add (continuous_id.div_const _)).mul hqdcont)
  have hrdвӮӮcont : Continuous rdвӮӮ :=
    (hqcont.const_mul _).add
      ((continuous_const.sub (continuous_id.div_const _)).mul hqdcont)
  refine вҹЁ(вҲ« x in (-6:в„қ)..0, |rdвӮҒ x|) + вҲ« x in (0:в„қ)..6, |rdвӮӮ x|, ?_, ?_вҹ©
  В· have h1 : 0 вүӨ вҲ« x in (-6:в„қ)..0, |rdвӮҒ x| :=
      intervalIntegral.integral_nonneg (by norm_num) fun x _ => abs_nonneg _
    have h2 : 0 вүӨ вҲ« x in (0:в„қ)..6, |rdвӮӮ x| :=
      intervalIntegral.integral_nonneg (by norm_num) fun x _ => abs_nonneg _
    exact add_nonneg h1 h2
  intro t ht
  have htI : ((t : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) вү  0 :=
    mul_ne_zero (Complex.ofReal_ne_zero.2 ht) Complex.I_ne_zero
  have hvder : вҲҖ x : в„қ, HasDerivAt
      (fun y : в„қ => Complex.exp (((t * y : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) / ((t : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I))
      (Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)) x := by
    intro x
    have h0 : (fun y : в„қ => ((t * y : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) =
        fun y : в„қ => ((t : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) * (y : в„Ӯ) := by
      funext y; push_cast; ring
    have h1 : HasDerivAt (fun y : в„қ => ((t * y : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)
        ((t : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) x := by
      rw [h0]
      simpa using (Complex.ofRealCLM.hasDerivAt (x := x)).const_mul ((t : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)
    have h2 := h1.cexp.div_const ((t : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)
    simpa [mul_div_cancel_rightвӮҖ _ htI] using h2
  have hsupp : вҲҖ x : в„қ, x вҲү Set.Icc (-6:в„қ) 6 вҶ’
      poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) = 0 := by
    intro x hx
    have h6 : 6 вүӨ |x| := by
      simp only [Set.mem_Icc, not_and_or, not_le] at hx
      rcases hx with h | h
      В· exact le_abs.2 (Or.inr (by linarith))
      В· exact le_abs.2 (Or.inl h.le)
    rw [poitouG_eq_zero h6, zero_mul]
  have hstep1 : poitouPhi (5 / 4 + t * Complex.I) =
      вҲ« x in (-6:в„қ)..6, poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) := by
    rw [poitouPhi_line_eq, вҶҗ setIntegral_eq_integral_of_forall_compl_eq_zero hsupp,
      integral_Icc_eq_integral_Ioc,
      вҶҗ intervalIntegral.integral_of_le (by norm_num : (-6:в„қ) вүӨ 6)]
  have hIcont : Continuous fun x : в„қ =>
      poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) :=
    continuous_poitouG.mul (Complex.continuous_exp.comp (by fun_prop))
  have hstep2 : (вҲ« x in (-6:в„қ)..6, poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)) =
      (вҲ« x in (-6:в„қ)..0, poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)) +
      вҲ« x in (0:в„қ)..6, poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) :=
    (intervalIntegral.integral_add_adjacent_intervals (hIcont.intervalIntegrable _ _)
      (hIcont.intervalIntegrable _ _)).symm
  have hcongrвӮҒ : (вҲ« x in (-6:в„қ)..0, poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)) =
      вҲ« x in (-6:в„қ)..0, (((1 + x / 6) * q x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) *
        Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I) := by
    refine intervalIntegral.integral_congr fun x hx => ?_
    rw [Set.uIcc_of_le (by norm_num : (-6:в„қ) вүӨ 0)] at hx
    have hodl : odlyzkoTestFn x = 1 + x / 6 := by
      rw [odlyzkoTestFn, abs_of_nonpos hx.2, max_eq_left (by linarith [hx.1])]
      ring
    have hval : poitouF x * Real.exp (3 / 4 * x) = (1 + x / 6) * q x := by
      rw [poitouF, hodl, hq]
      ring
    rw [poitouG, hval]
  have hcongrвӮӮ : (вҲ« x in (0:в„қ)..6, poitouG x * Complex.exp (((t * x : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) * Complex.I)) =
